# Release 4.0.4 -- Model Entrance Exam + Local Benchmarking

We've added a model "entrance exam" that runs automatically on every new model submission. The entrance exam, which acts as a gatekeeper for more in-depth model evaluation, tests each submitted against the latest BitMind image/video benchmarks generated by the subnet. Benchmark outputs include:
- ONNX model validation (input/output shape and dtype checks)
- pass/fail result (currently set to 80% minimum accuracy)
- metrics so miners know where they stand
- verbose output options that show what the data sources for each sample to help you drill down on your model's potential weak points

You can also now reproduce the exact entrance exam locally with gascli!
Run image benchmark: `gascli miner benchmark --image-model /path/image.onnx`
Run video benchmark: `gascli miner benchmark --video-model /path/video.onnx`

Useful options:
```
-v | -vv | -vvv: increase logging
--stream-images: stream images instead of downloading
--prune-old-data: remove older cached splits/configs after fetching the latest
```

### Generative Mining: A New Era of Creativity and Rewards
- Introducing the generative miner role! You'll generate high-quality images and videos based on prompts from validators.

  - The benchmark is dynamic for real-time relevance:
    - Static portion: Pulled from rotating Hugging Face datasets used in the subnet.
    - Dynamic portion: Continuously updated with new data from validators and generative miners, stored publicly on Hugging Face and integrated into evaluations in batches.
- This setup delivers a clearer picture of performance, stabilizes the incentive curve, and gives us the confidence to implement Winner-Takes-All (WTA) mechanics.

# GAS Mining Update: Dynamic Thresholding to Combat Performance Plateaus

Hi all, quick update on current competition status and what's to come!

**Current State:**
- Discriminative miners have been crushing it — top models are consistently hitting 95%+ accuracy in distinguishing real from synthetic content. The community’s progress has been phenomenal. But as models approach the ceiling of current benchmarks, it’s time to raise the bar, especially on image detection. 
- Over the next 24 hours, we’ll be introducing new challenge data designed to make benchmarks tougher and more dynamic. Future evaluations will draw more heavily from fresh, SN-generated samples, reducing overfitting and rewarding genuine adaptability.
- On the generative side, we’re seeing diminishing returns: most generations are coming from open source models and overlap with what our validators already produce. To drive true innovation, we’re prioritizing state-of-the-art, high-signal generations and improving verification to better reward novelty and quality (visual quality bonuses, C2PA bonus points, etc.). We have also tightened up generators' time-to-incentive down to approximately 2 hours.

**Up Next:**
Given the plateau and near impossible-to-beat thresholds described above, **we are enacting a temporary 90% burn of emissions**. This measure is to ensure economic sustainability of the SN while we transition to more difficult benchmarking and dynamic thresholding.
- During this transition, **benchmarking will remain paused for ~48 hours while the new datasets are integrated**. 
- Once complete, the threshold will reset based on prior winners’ performance against the expanded benchmark set. 
- With more effective generative miner output validation in place, future benchmark cycles will be have a tighter loop - higher signal data will be regularly integrated into benchmark runs, and this process of resetting thresholds based on top performers will be automated.
